body_html:
Your ops_to_register.h should have a line like this:
"ReductionOp<CPUDevice, float, int32, Eigen::internal::MinReducer>",
You can try adding this manually to see if you move past this error. How did you generate ops_to_register.h? I noticed that when I created the file using existing python script directly, I also got similar errors:
python tensorflow/python/tools/print_selective_registration_header.py --graphs="path to graph" > ops_to_register.h

But when I built the script using:
bazel build tensorflow/python/tools/print_selective_registration_header
and then:
./bazel-bin/tensorflow/python/tools/print_selective_registration_header --graphs="path to graph" > ops_to_register.h

I didn't get those errors.

Irrespective of above steps, I had to modify BUILD file to actually include those ops in the library.

Hope this helps!

body:
Your ops_to_register.h should have a line like this:
"ReductionOp<CPUDevice, float, int32, Eigen::internal::MinReducer<float>>",
You can try adding this manually to see if you move past this error. How did you generate ops_to_register.h? I noticed that when I created the file using existing python script directly, I also got similar errors:
python tensorflow/python/tools/print_selective_registration_header.py --graphs="path to graph" > ops_to_register.h

But when I built the script using:
bazel build tensorflow/python/tools/print_selective_registration_header
and then:
./bazel-bin/tensorflow/python/tools/print_selective_registration_header --graphs="path to graph" > ops_to_register.h

I didn't get those errors.

Irrespective of above steps, I had to modify BUILD file to actually include those ops in the library.

Hope this helps!
